    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="35"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/572: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Your No. 2, November 14. As you will recall, a proposed draft of trade
                    agreement was handed to the Brazilian Ambassador on <pb facs="0117" n="29"
                        xml:id="pg_29"/> October 30. The Brazilian experts are now engaged in
                    studying this draft in consultation with Rio de Janeiro.</p>
                <p>The inter-departmental sub-committee is actively studying possible concessions on
                    Argentine agricultural commodities as requested in the Argentine Ambassador’s
                    memorandum of October 7 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>]<note n="14" xml:id="d35fn14">
                        <ref target="frus1933v04#pg_661">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            661</ref>.</note> These studies should be completed within a few
                    days.</p>
                <p>The Colombian negotiations have made rapid progress and in the absence of
                    unforeseen difficulties should result in the signing of a trade agreement within
                    a few days.<note n="15" xml:id="d35fn15">Signed December 15, 1933; see <ref
                            target="#pg_217">pp. 217</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>We will telegraph further developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
